cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the accessibility features of mobile devices and proposes ways to improve them. The primary focus is on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO) as the authors suggest using sensors and machine learning to improve accessibility. The paper also touches on social and information retrieval aspects (cs.SD) as it discusses the importance of providing access to basic mobile applications. Additionally, the paper proposes using natural language processing (cs.CL) to improve accessibility. Finally, the paper discusses cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it suggests using encryption to protect sensitive user data.
